  "prompt": "Why mobile phone is also know as cell phone?",
  "response": "The term \"cell phone\" is derived from the cellular network technology that powers mobile phones. These networks use a system of distributed antennas and transmitters called \"cell sites\" or \"cell towers,\" which are strategically placed to cover specific geographic areas known as \"cells.\" Each cell is part of a larger network that allows mobile phones to communicate with each other and with landline phones.\n\nWhen a mobile phone user makes a call or sends a text message, the phone communicates with the nearest cell tower, which then relays the signal through the network to the recipient. The seamless handoff from one cell tower to another as a user moves ensures continued connectivity.\n\nHence, the term \"cell phone\" emphasizes the technology of cellular networks that enable mobile communication.",
